Genitalia:
Generally strongly sclerotized and dark. Segment IX annular, laterally setose; in lateral view, sternite IX forming a parallelogram, tergite IX narrower than sternite IX (
Fig. 9C
), in ventral view, sternum IX median margin widely and deeply ellipsoid (
Fig. 9E
