Fig. 9C
); in ventral and dorsal view, apices slightly curving laterad (
Fig. 9D, E
); pre-apical lateral processes absent. Inferior appendages each bipartite, setose; basal part broad in lateral and ventral view (
Figs 9C, E
), mesally concave, produced posteromesally into a broad, apically rounded lip, bearing small dorsal spines (
Fig. 9C, E
